org.soulwing.snmp

Interface VarbindCollection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<Varbind>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MutableVarbindCollection

    public interface VarbindCollection
extends Iterable<Varbind>
    A immutable ordered collection of Varbind objects resulting from an SNMP operation.
    Author:
    Carl Harris

      • nextIdentifiers

        List<String> nextIdentifiers(List<String> oids)
        Creates a list of object identifiers for a GETNEXT or GETBULK operation.

        The resulting list is a concatenation of the specified oids and the object identifiers associated with the varbinds in this collection, starting at index=oids.size(). This method allows you to easily construct a list of object identifiers where non-repeating objects identifiers are specified in the given oids and repeating object identifiers are extracted from the previously retrieved varbinds.

        Parameters:
        oids - array of object identifiers to prepend to the resulting list
        Returns:
        list of object identifiers starting with oids followed by the OIDS associated with the varbinds in this collection, starting at start.

      • nextIdentifiers

        List<String> nextIdentifiers(String... oids)
        Creates a list of object identifiers for a GETNEXT or GETBULK operation.

        The resulting list is a concatenation of the specified oids and the object identifiers associated with the varbinds in this collection, starting at index=oids.size(). This method allows you to easily construct a list of object identifiers where non-repeating objects identifiers are specified in the given oids and repeating object identifiers are extracted from the previously retrieved varbinds.

        Parameters:
        oids - array of object identifiers to prepend to the resulting list
        Returns:
        list of object identifiers starting with oids followed by the OIDS associated with the varbinds in this collection, starting at start.
